Quarter: The fiscal quarter being reported, e.g., 'Q1 2025'. This helps identify the time period for the financial data.
Logistics Costs: Total logistics costs for the quarter. This represents the expenditure on transportation, warehousing, and other logistics activities.
Percentage Change in Costs: The percentage change in logistics costs compared to the previous quarter. This metric helps to understand cost efficiency improvements or deteriorations.
Impact on Customer Trust: Indicates whether the logistics costs impact customer trust and after-sales support. This is a qualitative assessment of how logistics efficiency relates to customer satisfaction.
